# Email drafting & voice

> **DELETE OR REPLACE THIS FILE.** This is an example Tier 2 memory leaf showing the shape of a context-triggered feedback rule. Either delete it, or replace its contents with your own real voice rules. The `.example` suffix prevents Claude from loading it as a real leaf — once you have real content, save the file as `feedback_email_voice.md` (drop the `.example`).

Workflow gate: before drafting any email, READ this file. Do not start drafting until voice register is confirmed.

## Voice register

(Replace this section with the conventions you actually want Claude to follow.)

Example placeholders for the kinds of things that go here:

- **Salutation style.** First-name on first contact? "Dear ___" for formal? Different by audience?
- **Sign-off.** "Best", "Cheers", "Warm regards" — pick a default, name the exceptions.
- **Sentence length.** Short and direct, or measured paragraphs?
- **What to never say.** Phrases or framings the user has corrected before.

## Calibration loop

When the user edits one of your draft emails, READ this file and the diff together. If the edit reveals a pattern not yet captured here, append a one-liner under "Voice register" so the rule fires next time.

